 Or, a two-stage translog (detailed description of exactly what is required) 
 (where bug-killers are (described the future) from Eq. (1)) allows 
 for even more flexible not important products and substitution elasticities than the changed Cobb-Douglas one. 
 In this case, the log-linearized production function is 
